This was the view of stakeholders during the commemoration of the International Women’s Day, recently in Lagos.  Besides, the Bank said it has disbursed N37.9 billion to over 496 women-led enterprises as at December 2019.  Pitan said that the bank has a series of funding targeted at supporting women businesses at single-digit interest rates.
 
According to him, BoI is playing a key role to support the proposed first female-owned bank in Nigeria, which has the mandate to support women businesses.
 
Pitan stressed that there would be minimal development in Nigeria and Africa if efforts were not made to address some of the socio-economic impediments to limits women.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .